element.name: 1794_Digby_cache by inish, Traditional Cache (2/1.5)
element.description: This cache is near Dygby Bridge on the Grand Canal towpath.
element.long-description:
This cache is a clear lunchbox with blue borders. contains: logbook brio candle mask pocketgame "jewels" ;o) plastic tree badge
This cache is near Dygby Bridge on the Grand Canal towpath. The Grand Canal was built ca. 1756 to 1803 and links Dublin to the Shannon. Ireland's longest river.
The towpaths are always worth a visit. There are 2 long distance way marked ways The Barrow- and The Kildare Way and numerous looped ways and trails.
element.encoded-hints: Hidden in forked tree. Jack Daniels points the way.

ul.li:
2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by RosMcC
Pouring with rain, so wet to the knees in the undergrowth as well as wet from the head down in the rain - the joys of geocaching! Found quite quickly after a false start. TNLNSL Thanks

2010-06-10T19:00:00Z : Found it by thomasvm
Found it quickly while in the area - walked on the wrong side initially as well. Dropped a TB in. TFTC

2010-05-29T19:00:00Z : Found it by BlueFoxPL
Another great day for caching... found with some friends. TFTC.

2010-05-29T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wicca Cailín
Nineth find of ten today with Adam. Unfortunately walked down the wrong side of the canal to begin with but went back and took the right path. Found easily then. Log book very damp but still useable. TFTC
In: Bone Pen & Bouncing Ball Out: Marble

2010-05-08T19:00:00Z : Found it by merann
Nice spot, once the item mentioned in the hint was found the cache was found straight away.The log book is a tad damp and mouldy but still writtable. We didn't see any TB's in this cache. Out - Toy pig. In - Stencil. TFTC, Merann.
